      "prompt": "In the reaction where magnesium reacts with hydrochloric acid to form magnesium chloride and hydrogen gas, identify which species loses electrons (oxidation) and explain why the other species gains them in terms of electron transfer direction.",
      "answer": "Magnesium is oxidized because it loses two electrons. Hydrogen ions are reduced because they gain those electrons from the magnesium atoms during the reaction process to form neutral hydrogen gas molecules.",
