    {
      "prompt": "Given that chlorine gains an electron to become chloride, determine if this process is oxidation or reduction. Contrast the correct definition of oxidation with a common misconception where gain might be confused with loss.",
      "answer": "This process is reduction because it involves gaining electrons. Oxidation is defined as losing electrons; the common error occurs when one confuses 'gain' (reduction) with 'oxidization', mistakenly thinking that acquiring negative charge means oxidation occurred instead of reduction.",
      "rubric": "- Correctly classifies electron gain as reduction\n- Explicitly corrects the misconception regarding what constitutes oxidation",
      "skill": "critique"
